age_at_treatment_end.description: Subject Age in Days at End of Treatment Course Day Count

treatment_type.description: Text term that describes the kind of treatment administered.

treatment_agent.description: The name of the individual therapeutic agent(s) used as part of a treatment regimen.

id.description: A unique sequence of characters used to identify, name, or characterize an attribute shared by all members of a class.

treatment_response_id.description: In medicine, an improvement related to treatment. One or more characters used to identify, name, or characterize the nature, properties, or contents of a thing.

response.description: The result of an evaluation to determine whether pathologic and/or clinical changes resulted from treatment.

age_at_response.description: The age (in days) of subject when the response assessment was made.

response_category.description: A text term based on categorization of the pathologic and/or clinical changes that result from treatment, including eradication of detectable disease, stabilization of disease, or disease progression.
enum: Metastatic Soft Tissue and Bone Response

response_system.description: The type of standard from which a judgment concerning tumor response to therapy can be established.
